Sentencas: Alcohol solution precursor plasma spraying (SPPS) was employed to prepare porous La0.8Sr0.2MnO3 (LSM) cathode for solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: Microstructure and polarization of La0.8Sr0.2MnO3 cathode deposited by alcohol solution precursor plasma spraying

Sentencas: The surface morphology and microstructure of the LSM deposits were characterized by SEM.
Titulo: Microstructure and polarization of La0.8Sr0.2MnO3 cathode deposited by alcohol solution precursor plasma spraying

Sentencas: The electrochemical behavior was investigated through the impedance spectroscopy.
Titulo: Microstructure and polarization of La0.8Sr0.2MnO3 cathode deposited by alcohol solution precursor plasma spraying

Sentencas: The effect of annealing treatment on alcohol SPPS LSM microstructure and cathode polarization was examined.
Titulo: Microstructure and polarization of La0.8Sr0.2MnO3 cathode deposited by alcohol solution precursor plasma spraying

Sentencas: The results show that when the alcohol was used as solvent, at a spray distance of 60 mm, the as-sprayed LSM deposits presented porous agglomerates with a size range from 10 to 60 mu m which were mainly composed of small particles ranging from 0.2 to 2 mu m. The LSM cathode showed a finely porous microstructure with grain sizes from micrometers to submicrometers, Annealing at 1050 degrees C for 2 h in air resulted in coherent porous films of the perovskite phase with a fine microstructure.
Titulo: Microstructure and polarization of La0.8Sr0.2MnO3 cathode deposited by alcohol solution precursor plasma spraying

Sentencas: The electrochemical impedance measurement yielded the cathode polarization of 1.04 and 0.15 Omega.cm(2) for the ethanol SPPS LSM at 850 degrees C and 1000 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Microstructure and polarization of La0.8Sr0.2MnO3 cathode deposited by alcohol solution precursor plasma spraying
